cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Name: Peeping Tom vol3
cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Description: Always at the top of the lists of the best horror movies of all times, the unappreciated at its time masterpiece by Michael Powel, prophesied the slasher films that infested the genre decades later, and is still a fascinating study on the voyeurism of violence on the big screen. cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Name: Peeping Tom vol3 LOT1
cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Description: vo3 LOT1 As a kid, Mike Lewis was his own father’s guinea pig, in experiments on fear’s effect on the nervous system. All grown now, he’s an orphan and works in a photo studio. His main job is photographing young women, but his hobby is killing them with the camera as his weapon.
